{"data":{"mdx":null,"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Clay CSS Framework provides some utilities for you to work with  SCSS  and reuse it in your classes. Variables Mixins Functions Variablesâ€¦","timeToRead":2,"html":"<p class=\"clay-p\">Clay CSS Framework provides some utilities for you to work with <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com\">SCSS</a> and reuse it in your classes.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#variables\">Variables</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#mixins\">Mixins</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#functions\">Functions</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"clay-h2\">Variables</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Think of variables as a way to store information that you want to reuse throughout your stylesheet. You can store things like colors, font stacks, or any CSS value you think you'll want to reuse. Sass uses the $ symbol to make something a variable. <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com/guide\">SASS</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-container\">\n            <button class=\"btn btn-sm btn-copy\" title=\"Copy\"><svg class=\"lexicon-icon\"><use xlink:href=\"/images/icons/icons.svg#paste\"></use></svg></button>\n            <div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scss\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Alert Dismissible</span>\n\n<span class=\"token property\"><span class=\"token variable\">$alert-dismissible-padding-bottom</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span> <span class=\"token statement keyword\">!default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\"><span class=\"token variable\">$alert-dismissible-padding-left</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span> <span class=\"token statement keyword\">!default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token property\"><span class=\"token variable\">$alert-dismissible-padding-right</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 2.5rem <span class=\"token statement keyword\">!default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// 40px</span>\n<span class=\"token property\"><span class=\"token variable\">$alert-dismissible-padding-top</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token null\">null</span> <span class=\"token statement keyword\">!default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n        </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\"><a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/tree/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/variables\">All <strong>variables</strong> available</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 class=\"clay-h2\">Mixins</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Some things in CSS are a bit tedious to write, especially with CSS3 and the many vendor prefixes that exist. A mixin lets you make groups of CSS declarations that you want to reuse throughout your site. You can even pass in values to make your mixin more flexible. A good use of a mixin is for vendor prefixes. Here's an example for transform. <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com/guide\">SASS</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<div class=\"code-container\">\n            <button class=\"btn btn-sm btn-copy\" title=\"Copy\"><svg class=\"lexicon-icon\"><use xlink:href=\"/images/icons/icons.svg#paste\"></use></svg></button>\n            <div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scss\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><span class=\"token property\"><span class=\"token variable\">$map</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n\t<span class=\"token property\">bg</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'#0B5FFF'</span>,\n\t<span class=\"token comment\">//...</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token selector\">.my-button </span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">@include</span> <span class=\"token function\">clay-button-variant</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n        </div>\n<p class=\"clay-p\"><a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/blob/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/mixins/_buttons.scss#L1\">clay-button-variant#L1</a></p>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">You can find all mixins available by component if you want to create a component extension.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\"><a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/tree/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/mixins\">All <strong>mixins</strong> available</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 class=\"clay-h2\">Functions</h2>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Clay CSS provides some <strong>SCSS</strong> functions that help you be more productive. To learn more about <strong>functions</strong> see <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com/documentation/file.SASS_REFERENCE.html#function_directives\">sass-lang.com</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Sass ternary shorthand: <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">if($variable-name, true, false);</code>. See <a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/blob/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/functions/_global-functions.scss#L5\">setter#L5</a></p>\n<div class=\"code-container\">\n            <button class=\"btn btn-sm btn-copy\" title=\"Copy\"><svg class=\"lexicon-icon\"><use xlink:href=\"/images/icons/icons.svg#paste\"></use></svg></button>\n            <div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scss\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><span class=\"token comment\">// @param $var - The variable name</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @param $val - The default value</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">setter</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$var</span>, <span class=\"token variable\">$val</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n        </div>\n<p class=\"clay-p\">Helper for displaying warning messages for required variables. See <a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/blob/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/functions/_global-functions.scss#29\">required#L29</a></p>\n<div class=\"code-container\">\n            <button class=\"btn btn-sm btn-copy\" title=\"Copy\"><svg class=\"lexicon-icon\"><use xlink:href=\"/images/icons/icons.svg#paste\"></use></svg></button>\n            <div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"scss\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-scss\"><span class=\"token comment\">// @param $var - The variable to check</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// @param $msg - The error message</span>\n\n<span class=\"token function\">required</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$var</span>, <span class=\"token variable\">$msg</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n        </div>\n<blockquote>\n<p class=\"clay-p\"><a href=\"https://github.com/liferay/clay/blob/master/packages/clay-css/src/scss/functions/_global-functions.scss\">All <strong>functions</strong> available</a></p>\n</blockquote>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{"className":["clay-p"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Clay CSS Framework provides some utilities for you to work with "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://sass-lang.com"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SCSS"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and reuse it in your classes."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","p